{
  "stem": "19923.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 6.6,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You zigzag to avoid being hit.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And for some reason, they were able to single you out and identify you as Jewish from a distance.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Probably now, in my recollection, it's not because of what you looked like but because of the area in which you live.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "They knew you were Jewish because maybe you wore different clothing or perhaps you acted differently.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "But it was-- they knew you were Jewish.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And as soon as they saw you, if there were any group of children, they would immediately start picking up stones and start letting you have it.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And you had to run fast, as fast as you could, to avoid being hit by a stone.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 16,
      "text": "We were not allowed to go in the-- in the-- in the beginning, as my earliest recollections, [PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] they stopped allowing Jews, Jewish people, to go in public parks.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 17,
      "text": "And there was a public park in Cologne called Volksgarten, which mean People's Garden, and it had a small pond.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 18,
      "text": "And my father once took us there after the Germans had decreed that the Jews could not go, and they found him.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 19,
      "text": "They found my father.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 20,
      "text": "And they-- two Germans picked him up and were going to throw him in the water and drown him, when some officer came by and says, [GERMAN], you know, let the Jew go.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 21,
      "text": "And they just barely let a-- let him alive with the skin of his life.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 22,
      "text": "And they had-- they told us, get-- get out of here.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 23,
      "text": "But they didn't just say get out.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 24,
      "text": "They swore at us until we moved out of there, until we vacated.",
      "word_count": 13
    }
  ],
